HEADWORD: Three-quarter
<hw>Three"-quar`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Paint.)</fld>
<def>Measuring thirty inches by twenty-five; -- said of
portraitures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Three-quarter length</b></col>, <cd>a portrait showing
the figure to the hips only.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-score</ent>⟦br⟧
